{
  "texts": [
    "Given these ambiguities, this article investigates how copyright law might adapt to better address the challenges of AI-assisted and AI-generated works, aiming to support human creators while fostering AI innovation.",
    "Although AI technology can autonomously generate creative content, there are nuanced legal considerations.",
    "First, AI-generated content that results from minimal prompting still requires a re-examination of copyright protections, particularly regarding ownership, fair use in training datasets, and authorship rights (Jiang et al., 2023).",
    "Second, creatives using AI-assisted technologies should be eligible for copyright protection when they can demonstrate \"significant human contributions.\"",
    "Many artists meet these criteria by documenting their creative processes, using their own works to train models, and further refining AI-generated outputs post-production (Hutson et al., 2023)."
  ]
}